## This project simulates a virtual pet, similar to an old tomogachi. 
## It uses an advanced understanding of classes, constructors, and calling methods to have multiple classes overlap to create the virtual pet.
## The pet is it's own class, however the activities associated with the pet, such as feeding it or playing with it, are their own seperate classes for customization.
## That, combined with the activites embedded in the pet class, make for a functional little digital pet project. Literally.
  
